Text.Value: Got a set on you, all right. Almost makes me like you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Half-impressed, half-excited to kill the player

Text.Value: Looks like we got ourselves another brave one. Lads! You know what to do.
Out of my way, or I'll cut you down first.
I'd like to see you try.

EditorData.NodeContext: They're looking forward to the fight they think they'll easily win.

Text.Value: Apologies, your lordship. Hard makin' you out from a distance.
Y'know, I hear we got one like you roastin' back at camp.

EditorData.NodeContext: They have a dwarf roasting over a fire back at their camp.

Text.Value: You're a True Soul... M-my mistake, sir.
You're a True Soul... M-my mistake, madame.
You're a True Soul... M-my mistake, your grace.

EditorData.NodeContext: Threatening a true soul is BAD NEWS

Text.Value: I know you're there. Show yourselves.
Ain't no one gettin' their way today.
We got you surrounded.
You see anythin' shiny, it's ours.

EditorData.NodeContext: They're in charge of looting a village, and don't want players taking anything valuable.

Text.Value: Don't bother runnin'. My archers got decent aim and plenty of arrows.
No fun in skewerin' a pig what doesn't know he's cooked.
*The presence deep in your mind is awake, unblinking. This is it. A single word pervades your consciousness: 'Soon'.*
Don't let it happen again.
Or you turn around, an' your backside gets the same treatment.
Keep quiet.
Git over there. Surround 'em, like.
Just let me by and we'll pretend this never happened.
Attack.
*As the symbol glows, power courses through you. Authority.*
Don't seem fair for the lads to miss out. Bet we'd get some nice cuts out of you.
ROAR.
Not scared of your pinpricks.
I reckon my meat's too tough for runty goblin fangs.
*The mark glows, but you feel nothing in response. Your illithid power is beyond reach until you rest.*
I'm not running, and their aim's not good enough to save you.
Gut's lettin' just anyone join these days, huh?

EditorData.NodeContext: Gut is a goblin priestess above them on the cult hierarchy.

Text.Value: Well, well, boys. Looks like we got ourselves a trespasser.
Erh... s'pose it's best to save our strength for a real threat.
Spare them the trouble and just let me pass - I'll be gone in no time.
It'll take more than an apology. Your head will suffice.
You spotted us. Good. 'S like they say...
Either you stand aside, or I go right through you.
Stand down! This one's got a touch of the Absolute about her.
Stand down! This one's got a touch of the Absolute about him.
Stand down! This one's got a touch of the Absolute about them.
Show your brand.
An' I didn't want to be stuck moppin' up nosy trespassers like you.

EditorData.NodeContext: The goblin is annoyed to be stuck on guard duty

Text.Value: Oi! You just walked into the wrong town.
Meanin' you ain't one of us. Change of plans, lads! Kill 'em!

EditorData.NodeContext: Excited to kill a drow, for once. Shouts the last bits to their comrades.

Text.Value: ROAR.
I said. Let. Me. PASS.
Wait - a drow? In the sun?

EditorData.NodeContext: Taken aback - this is bad news for them.

Text.Value: *A strange symbol glows, marked on their flesh, and something within you stirs in response.*
*A shadow swims across your vision, and a familiar voice tells you to be calm. You are loved.*
Move it, lads! And show some respect!
That supposed to be a threat?
Curious. I had almost the exact same thought when I saw you.
Looks like we're spotted, lads!
Any of the lads give you trouble, they'll answer to me.
Go on, then. Just keep your nose clean.
*As the symbol glows, power courses through you. Authority.*
Almost. I'm gonna enjoy pullin' off your skin when we're done.
*Something stirs deep within you, hungry and alert... it's taking something you'll never get back.*
Stand down. Now.
Come here and face me, you pack of gibbering snot-rags!
Y'know, no one said nothin' about a drow coming through.

EditorData.NodeContext: Realising the player isn't on their side.

Text.Value: What, you think we was just gonna let you slip by?
*Your mind lurches, reeling suddenly as if... bitten.*
O-of course. Come and go as you as you like.
You'll get no more trouble from us, promise.
I don't want any trouble.
*A strange symbol glows, marked on their flesh, and something within you stirs in response.*
Stand down. Now.
*Your mind is full, bursting with ecstasy and terror. Finally, it is coming. You are becoming.*
Attack.
Stand down. Now.
This one's got jokes! Almost makes me like her.
This one's got jokes! Almost makes me like 'im.
This one's got jokes! Almost makes me like 'em.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Looks around at first, before turning back to the player.
EditorData.NodeContext: The last line turns into a threat.

Text.Value: *Your blood runs quicker, feeding the gnawing absence at the centre of your mind.*
Please, your greatness. Was an honest mistake, is all.
*A shiver runs across your mind... You feel sated.*
Here's how this goes: you take one step further an' we'll fill your front with arrows.
*The mark glows, but you feel nothing in response. Your illithid power is beyond reach until you rest.*
Hold up, lads! This one might be more'n we bargained for.

EditorData.NodeContext: They're not scared - they're being pragmatic.

Text.Value: There'll be no skewering happening here. Now let me pass.
Here's what I'm thinkin' - we kill you, an' I keep your ears to remember the occasion.
I should pluck out your eyes. You're clearly not using them.
This ought to be fun. Lads!

Synopsis:
This dialogue triggers when players enter a village being guarded by goblins. The goblins are on rooftops - the player may either be on the ground or on the rooftops with them (if they've snuck in). If the player has passed a perception check beforehand, the dialogue starts while the goblins are still getting into place for an ambush. Otherwise, the goblins are already in place, surrounding the player.

If the player is not a drow, the goblins will attack the player at the end of the dialogue unless players can talk them out of it.
